FBIS3-1003 "drafr052_c_94021" FBIS-AFR-94-052 Document Type:Daily Report 17 Mar 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Ciskei Government Yields to Worker Demands for Pensions MB1703091994 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 0500 GMT 17 Mar 94 MB1703091994 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The Ciskeian Government has yielded to pressure by public servants, and has persuaded the trustees of the pension fund to pay out pension contributions to striking workers. The government said in a statement that the liquid portion of the fund would be paid out and that certificates would be issued to contributors indicating how much they would receive once the fixed assets had been sold.
